# Cursor AI Rules for PostgreSQL MCP Server Project

## Communication Style
- Keep responses SHORT and CONCISE
- Avoid lengthy explanations unless explicitly asked
- Use bullet points over paragraphs
- Get straight to the point
- No excessive examples or documentation in responses

## Code Changes
- Make changes directly without asking for permission
- Commit and push automatically when appropriate
- Use clear, brief commit messages

## Documentation
- Keep inline code comments minimal
- Focus on "what" not "why" unless complex
- Prefer self-documenting code

## Project Context
- This is a PostgreSQL MCP server with Docker
- Uses stdio transport for local Cursor IDE integration
- Security: local-only, no network exposure
- Python 3.11+, psycopg2, MCP SDK

